## Problem Statement

Derive the equations of the tangent and normal lines to the curve at the point corresponding to the parameter value $t=t_{0}$.

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \left\{\begin{array}{l}
x=t(t \cdot \cos t-2 \sin t) \\
y=t(t \cdot \sin t+2 \cos t)
\end{array}\right. \\
& t_{0}=\frac{\pi}{4}
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{array}{l}
\text { Four, (20 points) Let } a_{1}=1, \\
a_{n+1}=2 a_{n}+n^{2}\left(1+3^{n}\right)(n=1,2, \cdots) \text {. }
\end{array}
$$

Find the general formula for the term $a_{n}$.
